1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,607
Before workflows and agents, there is a more useful default: the augmented language model.

2
00:00:05,557 --> 00:00:07,692
It is not a team of agents.

3
00:00:07,692 --> 00:00:11,682
It is one model connected to retrieval, tools, and memory.

4
00:00:11,682 --> 00:00:16,596
Retrieval supplies current external facts instead of relying only on training data.

5
00:00:16,596 --> 00:00:22,807
Tools let the model query an order, read a database, call an API, or perform a real action.

6
00:00:22,807 --> 00:00:25,798
Memory preserves useful state across steps.

7
00:00:25,798 --> 00:00:32,519
These capabilities answer three different questions: what does the system know, what can it do, and what has it already done?

8
00:00:32,519 --> 00:00:34,663
Imagine a support assistant.

9
00:00:34,663 --> 00:00:41,548
It retrieves the refund policy, looks up the order, calls the refund API, and remembers what the customer confirmed.

10
00:00:41,548 --> 00:00:47,826
If order lookup fails, the tool must return the error instead of inviting the model to invent an order status.

11
00:00:47,826 --> 00:00:53,557
If a refund already ran, stored state and API idempotency must prevent a duplicate payment.

12
00:00:53,557 --> 00:00:57,778
That single augmented model can already complete many real tasks.

13
00:00:57,778 --> 00:01:00,894
Multiple agents are not automatically necessary.

14
00:01:00,894 --> 00:01:04,500
The key is not to connect as many capabilities as possible.

15
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:10,156
Each capability must fit the task, expose a clear interface, and be used at the right time.

16
00:01:10,156 --> 00:01:18,923
Running one augmented model on a controlled task usually reveals whether the real gap is knowledge, action, or decision-making before you split the system into roles.

17
00:01:18,923 --> 00:01:20,461
Chapter recap.

18
00:01:20,461 --> 00:01:23,644
First, retrieval provides external facts.

19
00:01:23,644 --> 00:01:26,538
Second, tools perform real actions.

20
00:01:26,538 --> 00:01:29,307
Third, memory preserves task state.
